  "texts": [
    "Experts encode linguistic information in the form of feature vectors.",
    "A hypernetwork then learns to generate adapter weights for LoRA from the feature vectors.",
    "They demonstrate the impact of their fine-tuning approach on several GLUE tasks such as MNLI, RTE and so on.",
    "The dataset consists of variants of the GLUE benchmark for five dialects: African American Vernacular English (AAVE), Indian English (IndE), Nigerian English (NgE), Colloquial Singaporean English (CollSgE), and Chicano English (ChcE).",
    "Similarly, Liu et al. [2023] use dynamic aggregation of linguistic rules to adapt LLMs to multiple dialects."
  ],
